{
  "abstract": "Gliricidia sepium. The very name has a musical lilt that makes one want to wax lyrical about it. But the\r\nattraction doesn’t end with the name. Gliricidia is a fast-growing, tropical, leguminous tree that one\r\nscarcely notices. Yet it is ubiquitous. One passes it on highways and back roads. It is found in just\r\nabout any patch of wild trees and bushes.",
